info.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 13 at 10:17PM PST until January 14 at 4:00PM PST by NWS Eureka
info.description: ...WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 2 AM TO 4 PM PST SATURDAY... * WHAT...South winds 25 to 35 mph with gusts up to 45 mph expected. Locally stronger gusts over ridgetops and exposed terrain. * WHERE...Northern Humboldt Coast, Southwestern Humboldt and Northern Humboldt Interior Counties. Including the communities around Humboldt Bay, Trinidad, Orick and Shelter Cove. * WHEN...From 2 AM to 4 PM PST Saturday. * IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result.
info.instruction: Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.
